messages.message: hey everyone, I'm running instabase locally with celery and ari ocr to test a flow feature
ran into this error and not sure how to debug
i just wanted to run a pdf through ocr app to look at the ibocr

Have you checked the console logs? 

Also we generally use Process Files in Flow to run the OCR (the necessity of which is a UI/UX bug given the existence of a stand-alone OCR app, but good to know to get unblocked
Never seen the OCR “app” used outside of an Anant demo.
i usually run process files through ocr too, but i saw the OCR app so wanted to run it
looks like you've modified some code?
have you checked to see you don't get the error before your change?
yup i've modified a bunch in shared-utils/py-utils
in general you can see the logs in app-tasks, the stack trace should ideally show up there
i'll just make a flow and run process files to see if this is still a problem
"make build mypy" as well. that will tell you syntax errors that are going on in your code
